A BILL FOR AN ACT
RELATING TO HIGHWAY SAFETY.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF HAWAII:
1 SECTION 1. The legislature finds that skateboard accidents
2 on roadways and streets can result in serious injury to the
3 skateboard user, including head trauma. According to an article
4 published in the Journal of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgery,
5 "Injuries to the Head and Face from Skateboarding: A 10-Year
6 Analysis From National Electronic Injury Surveillance System
7 Hospitals", from 2009 to 2018, there were an estimated 100,201
8 emergency room visits nationwide related to trauma to the head
9 and face while skateboarding. The article concluded that "[aj
10 substantial number of [emergency department] visits were a
11 result of skateboarding-related facial trauma. Given the
12 neurologic outcomes of head trauma and functional consequences
13 of facial fractures, especially among adolescents, our findings
14 suggest that injury prevention programs and more aggressive
15 helmet use may be necessary to reduce morbidity and
16 hospitalization".
