1 The legislature further finds that existing laws in the
2 State protect bicyclists under the age of sixteen by requiring
3 operators to wear a helmet. Additionally, the legislature notes
4 that other states require helmets for minors, including
5 California, New York, and Oregon. Extension of similar safety
6 provisions for bicyclists to skateboard riders will provide
7 additional protection for all roadway users.
8 Accordingly, the purpose of this Act is to require the use
9 of a safety helmet by anyone under the age of eighteen while
10 riding a skateboard on public property.
11 SECTION 2. Chapter 291C, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
12 amended by adding a new section to part XII to be appropriately
•< designated and to read as follows:
AJ
14 "§291C- Skateboards; helmet required. (a) No person
15 under eighteen years of age shall operate a skateboard upon a
16 street, roadway, or bikeway, or any other public property,
17 unless the person is wearing a properly fitted and fastened
18 helmet that:
19 (1) Is designed to fit the user;
20 (2) Is designed to protect against head trauma; and
